{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":4831,"text":"George and Charlotte Blonsky, who were"},{"time":8237,"text":"a married couple living in\nthe Bronx in New York City,"},{"time":11609,"text":"invented something."},{"time":12854,"text":"They got a patent in\n1965 for what they call,"},{"time":16833,"text":"\"a device to assist women in giving birth.\""},{"time":22508,"text":"This device consists of a large, round table\n"},{"time":26438,"text":"and some machinery."},{"time":28191,"text":"When the woman is ready to deliver her child,"},{"time":31400,"text":"she lies on her back,"},{"time":32801,"text":"she is strapped down to the table,"},{"time":35232,"text":"and the table is rotated at high speed."},{"time":38311,"text":"The child comes flying out"},{"time":41736,"text":"through centrifugal force."},{"time":49717,"text":"If you look at their patent carefully,"},{"time":54246,"text":"especially if you have any\nengineering background or talent,"},{"time":58115,"text":"you may decide that you see"},{"time":59574,"text":"one or two points where the design is \nnot perfectly adequate. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66261,"text":"Doctor Ivan Schwab in California"},{"time":69030,"text":"is one of the people, \none of the main people,"},{"time":70984,"text":"who helped answer the question,"},{"time":72570,"text":"\"Why don't woodpeckers get headaches?\""},{"time":78281,"text":"And it turns out the answer to that"},{"time":79498,"text":"is because their brains"},{"time":81722,"text":"are packaged inside their skulls"},{"time":83493,"text":"in a way different from the way"},{"time":85993,"text":"our brains, we being human beings,"},{"time":88497,"text":"true, have our brains packaged."},{"time":92456,"text":"They, the woodpeckers, typically"},{"time":94839,"text":"will peck, they will bang their head"},{"time":97027,"text":"on a piece of wood thousands \nof times every day. Every day!"},{"time":102318,"text":"And as far as anyone knows,"},{"time":104231,"text":"that doesn't bother them in the slightest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105437,"text":"How does this happen?"},{"time":107703,"text":"Their brain does not slosh around like ours does."},{"time":110629,"text":"Their brain is packed in very tightly,"},{"time":113341,"text":"at least for blows coming \nright from the front."},{"time":116197,"text":"Not too many people paid attention"},{"time":118140,"text":"to this research until\nthe last few years"},{"time":121224,"text":"when, in this country especially,"},{"time":123839,"text":"people are becoming curious about"},{"time":125227,"text":"what happens to the brains\nof football players"},{"time":127422,"text":"who bang their heads repeatedly."},{"time":130150,"text":"And the woodpecker maybe relates to that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135218,"text":"There was a paper published"},{"time":137311,"text":"in the medical journal The Lancet"},{"time":139056,"text":"in England a few years ago called"},{"time":140486,"text":"\" A man who pricked his finger\nand smelled putrid for 5 years.\""},{"time":147903,"text":"Dr. Caroline Mills and her team"},{"time":149711,"text":"received this patient and didn't \nreally know what to do about it."},{"time":153810,"text":"The man had cut his finger,"},{"time":155670,"text":"he worked processing chickens,"},{"time":159143,"text":"and then he started to\nsmell really, really bad."},{"time":161579,"text":"So bad that when \nhe got in a room"},{"time":162798,"text":"with the doctors and the nurses,"},{"time":164115,"text":"they couldn't stand being \nin the room with him."},{"time":166874,"text":"It was intolerable."},{"time":168675,"text":"They tried every drug,"},{"time":170174,"text":"every other treatment\nthey could think of."},{"time":171992,"text":"After a year, he still \nsmelled putrid."},{"time":174223,"text":"After two years, still smelled putrid."},{"time":176032,"text":"Three years, four years,\nstill smelled putrid."},{"time":179262,"text":"After five years, it went away on its own."},{"time":182299,"text":"It's a mystery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185998,"text":"In New Zealand, Dr. Lianne Parkin"},{"time":188347,"text":"and her team tested an old \ntradition in her city."},{"time":193909,"text":"They live in a city that has huge hills,"},{"time":196636,"text":"San Francisco-grade hills."},{"time":198255,"text":"And in the winter there,\nit gets very cold"},{"time":200372,"text":"and very icy."},{"time":201556,"text":"There are lots of injuries."},{"time":203150,"text":"The tradition that they tested,"},{"time":205415,"text":"they tested by asking people"},{"time":207047,"text":"who were on their way to \nwork in the morning,"},{"time":209446,"text":"to stop and try something out."},{"time":211389,"text":"Try one of two conditions."},{"time":213392,"text":"The tradition is that in the winter,"},{"time":216145,"text":"in that city, you wear your socks\non the outside of your boots."},{"time":220861,"text":"And what they discovered by experiment,"},{"time":224260,"text":"and it was quite graphic when they saw it,"},{"time":226429,"text":"was that it's true."},{"time":227844,"text":"That if you wear your socks on the \noutside rather than the inside,"},{"time":231163,"text":"you're much more likely \nto survive and not slip and fall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236516,"text":"Now, I hope you will agree\nwith me that these things"},{"time":241894,"text":"I've just described to you,"},{"time":244109,"text":"each of them, deserves some kind of prize.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":250289,"text":"And that's what they got,"},{"time":251924,"text":"each of them got an Ig Nobel prize."},{"time":255199,"text":"In 1991, I, together with bunch of other people,"},{"time":259191,"text":"started the Ig Nobel prize ceremony."},{"time":262094,"text":"Every year we give out 10 prizes."},{"time":265026,"text":"The prizes are based on just \none criteria. It's very simple."},{"time":272009,"text":"It's that you've done something that \nmakes people laugh and then think."},{"time":277993,"text":"What you've done makes \npeople laugh and then think."},{"time":281837,"text":"\nWhatever it is, there's something about it"},{"time":283845,"text":"\nthat when people encounter it at first,"},{"time":286582,"text":"their only possible reaction is to laugh."},{"time":289893,"text":"And then a week later,"},{"time":291816,"text":"it's still rattling around in their heads"},{"time":293507,"text":"and all they want to do \nis tell their friends about it."},{"time":296267,"text":"That's the quality we look for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298465,"text":"Every year, we get in the neighborhood"},{"time":301250,"text":"of 9,000 new nominations \nfor the Ig Nobel prize."},{"time":305692,"text":"Of those, consistently between 10 percent"},{"time":308521,"text":"and 20 percent of those nominations"},{"time":311004,"text":"are people who nominate themselves."},{"time":314914,"text":"Those self-nominees almost never win."},{"time":318881,"text":"It's very difficult, numerically, \nto win a prize if you want to."},{"time":323200,"text":"Even if you don't want to,"},{"time":325045,"text":"it's very difficult numerically."},{"time":327761,"text":"You should know that when \nwe choose somebody"},{"time":331411,"text":"to win an Ig Nobel prize,"},{"time":332683,"text":"We get in touch with that person, very quietly."},{"time":336259,"text":"We offer them the chance to decline"},{"time":338820,"text":"this great honor if they want to."},{"time":342202,"text":"Happily for us, almost everyone \nwho's offered a prize"},{"time":345526,"text":"decides to accept."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349035,"text":"What do you get if you\nwin an Ig Nobel prize?"},{"time":351976,"text":"Well, you get several things."},{"time":353553,"text":"You get an Ig Nobel prize."},{"time":357083,"text":"The design is different every year."},{"time":359414,"text":"These are always handmade\nfrom extremely cheap materials."},{"time":364220,"text":"You're looking at a picture"},{"time":365881,"text":"of the prize we gave last year, 2013."},{"time":369910,"text":"Most prizes in the world also give"},{"time":371946,"text":"their winners some cash, some money."},{"time":376644,"text":"We don't have any money,"},{"time":377707,"text":"so we can't give them."},{"time":379218,"text":"In fact, the winners have to\npay their own way"},{"time":382094,"text":"to come to the Ig Nobel ceremony,"},{"time":384898,"text":"which most of them do."},{"time":386761,"text":"Last year, though, we did manage\nto scrape up some money."},{"time":389754,"text":"Last year, each of the 10\nIg Nobel prize winners"},{"time":394265,"text":"received from us 10 trillion dollars."},{"time":400043,"text":"A $10 trillion bill from Zimbabwe. (Laughter)"},{"time":405476,"text":"You may remember that \nZimbabwe had a little adventure"},{"time":408300,"text":"for a few years there of inflation."},{"time":410895,"text":"They ended up printing bills"},{"time":412515,"text":"that were in denominations as\nlarge as 100 trillion dollars."},{"time":416371,"text":"The man responsible, who runs\nthe national bank there, by the way,"},{"time":419156,"text":"won an Ig Nobel prize in mathematics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421929,"text":"The other thing you win is an invitation"},{"time":423681,"text":"to come to the ceremony,"},{"time":425184,"text":"which happens at Harvard University."},{"time":426926,"text":"And when you get there,"},{"time":428061,"text":"you come to Harvard's biggest \nmeeting place and classroom."},{"time":430778,"text":"It fits 1,100 people,"},{"time":432063,"text":"it's jammed to the gills,"},{"time":433189,"text":"and up on the stage,"},{"time":434020,"text":"waiting to shake your hand,"},{"time":435814,"text":"waiting to hand you your Ig Nobel prize,"},{"time":438086,"text":"are a bunch of Nobel prize winners."},{"time":440735,"text":"That's the heart of the ceremony."},{"time":442034,"text":"The winners are kept secret until that moment,"},{"time":444184,"text":"even the Nobel laureates \nwho will shake their hand"},{"time":446611,"text":"don't know who they are\nuntil they're announced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449854,"text":"I am going to tell you \nabout just a very few"},{"time":452974,"text":"of the other medical-related prizes we've given."},{"time":456028,"text":"Keep in mind, we've given 230 prizes. \n"},{"time":458284,"text":"There are lots of these people\nwho walk among you."},{"time":460578,"text":"Maybe you have one."},{"time":462698,"text":"A paper was published about 30 years ago"},{"time":464842,"text":"called \"Injuries due to Falling Coconuts.\""},{"time":467352,"text":"It was written by Dr. Peter Barss,"},{"time":469307,"text":"who is Canadian."},{"time":471518,"text":"Dr. Barss came to the ceremony"},{"time":473704,"text":"and explained that as a young doctor,"},{"time":475571,"text":"he wanted to see the world."},{"time":477052,"text":"So he went to Papua New Guinea."},{"time":479341,"text":"When he got there, he went to work\nin a hospital, and he was curious"},{"time":481680,"text":"what kinds of things happen to people\nthat bring them to the hospital."},{"time":487195,"text":"He looked through the \nrecords, and he discovered"},{"time":488493,"text":"that a surprisingly large number of people"},{"time":491283,"text":"in that hospital were there"},{"time":492449,"text":"because of injuries due to falling coconuts."},{"time":495996,"text":"One typical thing that happens is"},{"time":497782,"text":"people will come from the highlands,\nwhere there are not many coconut trees,"},{"time":501581,"text":"down to visit their relatives on the coast,"},{"time":503829,"text":"where there are lots."},{"time":505289,"text":"And they'll think that a coconut tree"},{"time":506679,"text":"is a fine place to stand and maybe lie down."},{"time":509348,"text":"A coconut tree that is 90 feet tall,"},{"time":511955,"text":"and has coconuts that weigh two pounds"},{"time":514178,"text":"that can drop off at any time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518230,"text":"A team of doctors in Europe"},{"time":520023,"text":"published a series of papers\nabout colonoscopies."},{"time":523532,"text":"You're all familiar with colonoscopies,"},{"time":525562,"text":"one way or another."},{"time":526854,"text":"Or in some cases,"},{"time":528169,"text":"one way and another."},{"time":531674,"text":"They, in these papers,"},{"time":535023,"text":"explained to their fellow doctors\nwho perform colonoscopies,"},{"time":539191,"text":"how to minimize the chance"},{"time":541162,"text":"that when you perform a colonoscopy,"},{"time":543823,"text":"your patient will explode. (Laughter)"},{"time":547413,"text":"Dr. Emmanuel Ben-Soussan"},{"time":549373,"text":"one of the authors,"},{"time":550547,"text":"flew in from Paris to the ceremony,"},{"time":553706,"text":"where he explained the history of this,"},{"time":555597,"text":"that in the 1950s,"},{"time":556773,"text":"when colonoscopies were becoming\na common technique for the first time,"},{"time":562101,"text":"people were figuring out how to do it well."},{"time":564740,"text":"And there were some difficulties at first."},{"time":567500,"text":"The basic problem, I'm sure you're familiar with,"},{"time":571471,"text":"that you're looking inside a \nlong, narrow, dark place."},{"time":576800,"text":"And so, you want to have a larger space."},{"time":580355,"text":"You add some gas to inflate it"},{"time":582486,"text":"so you have room to look around."},{"time":584400,"text":"Now, that's added to the \ngas, the methane gas,"},{"time":587127,"text":"that's already inside."},{"time":588635,"text":"The gas that they used at first,\nin many cases, was oxygen."},{"time":591635,"text":"So they added oxygen to methane gas."},{"time":594084,"text":"And then they wanted to be able to see,"},{"time":595799,"text":"they needed light,"},{"time":597047,"text":"so they'd put in a light source,"},{"time":598452,"text":"which in the 1950s was very hot."},{"time":600228,"text":"So you had methane gas, which is flammable,"},{"time":603546,"text":"oxygen and heat."},{"time":606338,"text":"They stopped using oxygen pretty quickly.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":611476,"text":"Now it's rare that patients will explode,"},{"time":613997,"text":"but it does still happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619736,"text":"The final thing that I want \nto tell you about is a prize"},{"time":623311,"text":"we gave to Dr. Elena Bodnar."},{"time":625742,"text":"Dr. Elena Bodnar invented a brassiere"},{"time":629867,"text":"that in an emergency"},{"time":631425,"text":"can be quickly separated \n"},{"time":632618,"text":"into a pair of protective face masks."},{"time":636137,"text":"One to save your life,"},{"time":637904,"text":"one to save the life of some \nlucky bystander. (Laughter)"},{"time":643228,"text":"Why would someone do this, you might wonder."},{"time":646255,"text":"Dr. Bodnar came to the ceremony"},{"time":648387,"text":"and she explained that \nshe grew up in Ukraine."},{"time":651348,"text":"She was one of the doctors who treated victims"},{"time":653064,"text":"of the Chernobyl power plant meltdown."},{"time":655108,"text":"And they later discovered that"},{"time":657692,"text":"a lot of the worst medical problems"},{"time":659617,"text":"came from the particles people breathed in."},{"time":661739,"text":"So she was always thinking after that"},{"time":663667,"text":"about could there be some simple mask\n"},{"time":665294,"text":"that was available everywhere\nwhen the unexpected happens."},{"time":669990,"text":"Years later, she moved to America."},{"time":671603,"text":"She had a baby,"},{"time":672447,"text":"One day she looked, and on the floor,"},{"time":674203,"text":"her infant son had picked up her bra,"},{"time":677274,"text":"and had her bra on his face."},{"time":679133,"text":"And that's where the idea came from."},{"time":680814,"text":"She came to the Ig Nobel ceremony"},{"time":682817,"text":"with the first prototype of the bra"},{"time":685157,"text":"and she demonstrated:"},{"time":689511,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":718265,"text":"[\"Paul Krugman, Nobel laureate \n(2008) in economics\"]"},{"time":748574,"text":"[\"Wolfgang Ketterle, Nobel \nlaureate (2001) in physics\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":763663,"text":"I myself own an emergency bra. (Laughter)"},{"time":767283,"text":"It's my favorite bra,"},{"time":769621,"text":"but I would be happy to \nshare it with any of you,"},{"time":772273,"text":"should the need arise."},{"time":774122,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":775078,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}